sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_049_CSMS (Table 172, doc pages 146-147 / PDF pages 43-44)
    Note over CP,CS: Reservation of a Charge Point - Transaction
    Note over CP,CS: Prerequisite: Central System supports Reservation feature profile

    CS->>CP: 1. ReserveNow.req
    Note left of CS: reservationId: <unique id><br/>connectorId: 0<br/>idTag: <Configured Valid IdTag><br/>expiryDate: <future timestamp> (*)
    Note left of CS: Validation: connectorId must be 0

    CP-->>CS: 2. ReserveNow.conf

    CP->>CS: 3. StatusNotification.req (status: Reserved)
    Note over CP: Validation: status must be Reserved
    CS-->>CP: 4. StatusNotification.conf

    Note over CP,CS: Expected: Only the idTag from the reservation<br/>can charge, on any available connector.<br/>CS accepts reservation for the right idTag and reservationId.
    Note over CP,CS: (*) expiryDate required by OCPP spec but not<br/>explicitly listed in the document's scenario step 1
